docs/coherence-foundations.md:184:When a system uses multiple LLM providers (Claude, GPT, Gemini, local models), each with different capabilities and failure modes, governance rules cannot be embedded in any single model's system prompt. They must be externalized into infrastructure that evaluates all models' outputs uniformly. PromptClaw's constitution is model-agnostic: it evaluates text output regardless of which agent or model produced it.
