my-claw/tools/workspace/claude_1774485834.md:65:## Recommended Architecture
my-claw/tools/workspace/claude_1774485834.md:78:Keep actions as **pure functions** (take state, return new state). Storage is the only side-effectful layer. This makes testing trivial and platform integration clean — Telegram handler and CLI handler both just call `on_command()`, which loads state, applies decay, applies action, saves state, returns rendered output.
my-claw/tools/workspace/task_81b9b618.md:13:**To use it**, you'll need to set `GEMINI_API_KEY` in your environment. The default model is `gemini-2.0-flash-exp` (overridable via `GEMINI_IMAGE_MODEL` env var). You can update the model to `gemini-2.5-flash-image` or `gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview` once you confirm which is available on your API key.
